author: @chicmalyshka888
text: With them being so professional I would have expected the company ask them to train before just putting them in the middle of the rink like that 😭 It only really takes about 30-60mins to be able to skate decently, but still, the way they’re just going out there suddenly. What helped me, was when I first got into the rink I started from the side. Holding onto the railing, and understanding the foot movements and patterns that were necessary. Afterwards, I distanced myself and learned to move at a steadier pace. From my own perspective, it looks like they’re going out into a war zone after putting their uniforms on for the first time. Maybe I’m exaggerating that completely. It’s great to see the staff and other members helping them out though. Teamwork makes the dream work

author: @mariyamajaz
text:
Kim Namjoon was first member to join BTS. His mom opposed him joining BTS because she wanted him to study well. He used to work so hard with the productions yet his mom would break his computers and mics so that he would concentrate on his studies. 

Kim Seokjin , who joined because of his visuals, got criticized that he had no talent in singing but he proved all of them wrong. He wanted to make his mom proud and wanted his mom to have something to brag about her son to their judgmental neighbors.

Min Yoongi , whose parents didn't support him well in his music career, had to manage his life on his own. If he had to take the bus, he didn't have money to eat. If he spent it on food, he couldn't take the bus. But now, he's earning millions.

Jung Hoseok  had earlier auditioned in JYP but was not accepted in the later half. Being a street dancer and having so much talent, he almost gave up and wanted to leave BTS but his members apposed him in that and he definitely didn't let them down. Yet, he was judged because of his visuals. He auditioned because he wanted his father to be proud of him.

Park Jimin , who had to starve himself only because people called him 'fat'. He came all the way from Busan to persuade his dreams and used to practice so much that once he slept for only 3 hours. That is what has made him perfect today.

Kim Taehyung lived with his grandmother for 15 years to support her in her farm. He had always been a part of BTS but was never shown in any promotion-not until they debut. Taehyung said he used to practice filming log so that when he's finally announced as a member he can do a lot of for his fans.

Jeon Jungkook came to Seoul from Busan in  a very young age persuade his dream. He even traveled all the way to America to learn dancing. Once Jimin caught him crying alone and when Jimin asked why, Jungkook said that he misses his family.

BTS , they might be global legends today but they had their own hardships too. So please stop calling them overrated and learn to respect them. They deserve what they're getting today

author: @lievekattenares2288
text: This is why I love BTS. They're not only  an amazing talented artist, but also wonderful-adorable human being. This video shows that BTS always supports and helps each other. If someone can't do something, they don't mocked or insulted him, instead they showed support and cheering him up. Just like when JHope and V who were just learning how to do roller skate were about to fall, the other members instinctively were ready to help  and protect so that they don't fall. In addition, when Jimin did a spin, V genuinely praised and then asked Jimin to show his cool spinning moves once again. Always love seeing their beautiful friendship ^__^

시간이 늦어서 그들을 볼 기회가 없었습니다. 그러나 다시 그들은 고통을 사랑합니다. 그가 그를 얼마나 사랑하는지 당신은 알고 있습니다. 때때로 우리가 당신이 그것에 따라 살기를 원하지 않기 때문에 어떤 일에 대해 침묵할 필요가 없을 때 그것이 얼마나 고통스러운지 압니까?
퍼플하츠의 세계를 소개해주셔서 감사합니다.
무슨 일이 일어나든 우리는 당신의 팔이고 당신의 군대입니다. 이전에 우리는 당신 자신의 길을 닦았고 당신은 마음의 평화를 가지고 그 길을 걸을 것입니다. 우리에게 문제가 있을 때 당신에 대해 생각하는 것만으로도 문제를 해결하고 마음과 정신을 진정시키기에 충분합니다. 당신의 고통을 우리와 함께 나누십시오. 아랍인들은 슬퍼할 때 강하다.✨💜💜
